FBIS4-42279 "drweu105_q_94015" FBIS-WEU-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 TURKEY `Terrorists' Killed in Erzincan Clash `Terrorists' Killed in Erzincan Clash TA3105114294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 GMT 31 May 94 TA3105114294 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report] [Text] In a clash that broke out between security forces and terrorists in the rural sector of Erzincan's Uzumlu District, 19 terrorists were killed. Four members of the security forces were martyred in the clash. The clash with the terrorists is said to be continuing in the region. Meanwhile, Erzincan Governor Recep Yazicioglu held a meeting on terrorist incidents with representatives of political parties and mass organizations in the province. Yazicioglu said that the terrorist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] organization is trying to divide the country using Alawite-Sunni and Turkish-Kurdish differences. He asked the people not to be deceived by such schemes.
